uency\nrange and for arbitrary angles. An isotropic distribution is considered, but\nthe methods used here can be easily applied to more general anisotropic\ndistributions, such as the bi-kappa or product-bi-kappa.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Nov 2015 19:10:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Jan 2016 17:03:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-23"}
