vortex dust', which contains remnants of disrupted earlier\nstructures not yet transferred to surviving ones. A combination of these\nprocesses is shown to cause an apparently nearly continuous increase in\nstructure size with downstream distance at {\\lambda} = 1, of the kind reported\nby D'Ovidio & Coats (2013)and attributed to mixing transition ...\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Nov 2015 10:07:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-19"}
