 and collisional data, even\nin such a highly-charged ion as Fe $^{20+}$, and to treat resonances\nnon-perturbatively. This is of particular importance for Fe ions given their\nimportance in the spectroscopic diagnostic modelling of astrophysical plasmas.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Nov 2015 13:46:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 20 Feb 2016 22:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 11 Apr 2016 17:32:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-12"}
